BARD INSTRUMENTS

Bards begin with their familiar guild lute. Alternate instruments can be
carried and selected with:

  instrument
  instrument <name>
  instrument off

The selected instrument shapes your newer battle songs. It does not replace
your guild soul, and you can return to the base lute at any time.

Alternate instruments are sold at the Bard Shoppe in the Darkwind Bard
guildhall.

Current instruments:

  drums        Rhythm songs, Rally, follower songs, and support timing hit
               harder and force pulse-style propagation.
  flute        Slightly improves Melody and Dissonance, and unlocks
               Whisper Canticle. Especially good for Soothe and Otto.
  violin       Greatly improves Dissonance morale pressure, social reputation
               songs, and damage-oriented dread.
  horn         Pushes songs into echo-style propagation and strengthens
               room-wide support, follower songs, and Finales.
  chimes       Improves Harmony, lore reads, control precision, and unlocks
               Mirror Refrain.
  concert lute Extends song field duration and helps social, lore, and craft
               performances linger.
  war harp     Improves Harmony and Crescendo battle support and helps hold
               enemy attention. Strong with support and damage pressure.

Archetypes have favored instruments. When your archetype, instrument, active
song fields, and command all point in the same direction, the command can gain
more force, longer duration, stronger morale pressure, better success odds, or
special flavor.

Use bscore or bmon to see your currently selected instrument.

New Bards should not panic about instruments immediately. Your lute works, and
fix lute can restore it. Instruments become more important as you learn more
song forms, unlock instrument-specific songs, and choose an archetype.

